Kenya's Deputy Environment Minister, Maathai, aims to reduce plastic bag usage due to their role in mosquito breeding and malaria risk.
The UN Environment Programme supports banning plastic bags in Kenya.
Eritrea has successfully transitioned to cotton and nylon bags.
San Francisco and other cities propose fees on plastic bags to reduce waste.
Rwanda and Uganda have implemented bans on plastic bags to protect the environment.
Tanzania is establishing a recycling plant to address plastic waste.
These efforts reflect a growing global trend towards reducing plastic pollution and promoting sustainable practices.
